column6: Kind of fit small, normally I wear a size 4 in all pants and leggings but I ordered these in a 4 and they were extremely tight. I feel like I am always pulling them up and this can get in the way when trying to walk or workout. I love the color and look however I feel like they are not very high waisted and do not stay on my waist. I also feel like if I pull them up a lot they become shorter on my legs. These have also started to loose quality after only one or two washes and a few wears. I usually love Lululemon leggings but these ones were very disappointing.

column6: I've had these tights for almost two years now and have loved them. I own several other lulu yoga pants that I love too, and at most wore these once a week. But then, on this fateful day, I put my beloved wunder unders on, only to find a hole in the bottom! Not at the seam... right in the middle of my right butt cheek. I've had pants for longer, worn pants more, and none have done this. I assume it is the brushed fabric. What makes it so buttery soft also makes it SO fragile. Alas... not sure I will invest in brushed items again. :( What other fabrics are just as soft as the brushed?
